to give birth to a child

sentences.english: The last stage of the birth process involves the delivery of the placenta, which is now called the afterbirth.
sentences.chinese: 分娩的最后一个阶段是胎盘的出来。

sentences.english: The doctor said my wife was too near her term to travel by air.
sentences.chinese: 医生说我的妻子离分娩期很近，不宜乘飞机旅行。

sentences.english: Month seven is also the month when the Lamaze classes begin.
sentences.chinese: 个月还是开始上无痛分娩课的月份。

sentences.english: OBJECTIVE To explore the full-term pregnancy the amniotic fluid of pregnant women decreased vaginal delivery security.
sentences.chinese: 目的探讨足月妊娠羊水偏少的孕妇阴式分娩的安全性。

sentences.english: I had gas and air, pethidine and then the epidural, which was bliss.
sentences.chinese: 那么我可以无痛分娩了，这真是有福气的事。

sentences.english: Objective To study the role of the overall deli very monitoring in decreasing the case mortality rate of perinatal children.
sentences.chinese: 目的探讨分娩全程监护在降低围生儿病死率中的作用。

sentences.english: Objective To decrease the injury rate and mortality of breech delivery during perinatal period.
sentences.chinese: 目的降低臀位分娩时围产儿的损伤率及病死率。

sentences.english: Different childbirth ways have in various degree influence on children's intelligence.
sentences.chinese: 不同的分娩方式对儿童智力有不同程度的影响。

sentences.english: After natural parturition, the growth of baby mice had been in normal.
sentences.chinese: 自然分娩后，新生动物发育生长正常。

sentences.english: The term "breech presentation" refers to the mother's position on the delivery table while giving birth.
sentences.chinese: “臀先露”定义为产妇分娩时在产床上的体位。

sentences.english: The term "quickening" refers to the rising pulse rate during the second stage of labor.
sentences.chinese: 术语“胎动”定义为分娩的第二产程期间加快的脉搏。

sentences.english: She is due to give birth to her first child with Prince William next month.
sentences.chinese: 她将在下个月分娩与威廉王子的第一个孩子。

sentences.english: Every minute a woman is dying from complications in pregnancy and childbirth.
sentences.chinese: 每分钟就有一名妇女死于怀孕和分娩并发症。

sentences.english: Also, remember that overnight deliverers currently do not pickup on Saturday or Sunday.
sentences.chinese: 要记住，即将分娩的母犬可不会挑周六或是周日。

sentences.english: Every day, 1500 women die from pregnancy- or childbirth-related complications.
sentences.chinese: 每天有1500名妇女死于妊娠或分娩相关的并发症。
